And the last testimonial, so to speak,
comes from Microtech,

01:07:11.180 --> 01:07:15.120
and I'd like to introduce Kristen Lee to
talk about their experiences.

01:07:15.350 --> 01:07:16.910
Hey Kristen.

01:07:18.900 --> 01:07:23.530
Hi, my name is Kristen Lee.

01:07:23.540 --> 01:07:27.780
I am Marketing Project Manager for
Microtech.

01:07:27.780 --> 01:07:31.040
We manufacture consumer and
professional scanners and also develop

01:07:31.040 --> 01:07:32.900
the software that controls them.

01:07:32.900 --> 01:07:35.900
We have a little bit different story.

01:07:35.900 --> 01:07:40.130
Our initial plan for releasing
our professional scanner,

01:07:40.130 --> 01:07:43.900
or scanning software,
was to port it to Carbon,

01:07:43.900 --> 01:07:46.710
add Aqua icons to it, and ship it.

01:07:46.900 --> 01:07:50.740
While this made sense for us,
we have a very complex UI,

01:07:50.950 --> 01:07:55.030
